%5C%22%3EAI%20Mode%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20could%20be%20bad%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddit-ad-revenue-grows-fastest-among-social-media-platforms-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EReddit%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReddit%20has%20grown%20significantly%20over%20the%20past%20year%2C%20thanks%20in%20large%20part%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddits-success-tied-to-google-search-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGoogle%20prioritizing%20Reddit%3C%2Fa%3E%20links%20in%20its%20search%20results%20and%20because%20searchers%20are%20often%20looking%20for%20human%20input%20on%20an%20internet%20increasingly%20dominated%20by%20AI%20and%20automated%20bots.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogles-vision-for-search-in-an-ai-era-gemini-io-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGoogle%20I%2FO%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20week%2C%20Google%20CEO%20Sundar%20Pichai%20described%20AI%20Mode%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Btotal%20overhaul%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20company's%20search%20tool.%20AI%20Mode%20will%20offer%20users%20a%20more%20conversational%20experience%2C%20rather%20than%20the%20traditional%20list%20of%20links.%20That%20means%20Google%20can%20give%20a%20user%20information%20found%20on%20Reddit%2C%20without%20that%20user%20ever%20having%20to%20visit%20the%20site.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20will%20mostly%20affect%20Reddit's%20logged-out%20users%2C%20who%20are%20more%20casual%20visitors%20without%20their%20own%20accounts.%20Logged-in%20users%20are%20Reddit's%20everyday%20fans.%20Much%20of%20Reddit's%20growth%20is%20with%20logged-out%20users%20coming%20through%20Google%20Search.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Monday%2C%20Reddit's%20stock%20dropped%20about%205%25%20after%20Wells%20Fargo%20said%20it%20expected%20Reddit%20traffic%20to%20decrease%20as%20%26quot%3BGoogle%20more%20aggressively%20implements%20AI%20features%20in%20search.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20wasn't%20the%20first%20time%20that%20changes%20to%20Google's%20search%20feature%20caused%20Reddit's%20stock%20to%20fall.%20Shares%20of%20the%20company%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddit-stock-drops-google-algorithm-tweak-hurt-its-user-growth-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efell%20by%20over%2015%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20February%20after%20Huffman%20said%20in%20an%20earnings%20call%20that%20the%20site%20saw%20traffic%20%26quot%3Bvolatility%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20fourth%20quarter%20after%20Google%20tweaked%20its%20search%20algorithm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20algorithms%20are%20often%20shifting%20(just%20ask%20a%20digital%20news%20organization)%2C%20Wells%20Fargo%20said%20recent%20user%20disruptions%20on%20Reddit%20are%20%26quot%3Blikely%20more%20permanent%26quot%3B%20as%20search%20behavior%20changes%20in%20response%20to%20Google's%20AI%20advancements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReddit%2C%20however%2C%20says%20that%20its%20logged-in%20users%2C%20who%20come%20to%20Reddit%20directly%2C%20are%20the%20primary%20driver%20of%20its%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20our%20product%20work%20allows%20us%20to%20develop%20and%20consistently%20grow%20those%20logged-in%20users%2C%20which%20are%20the%20bedrock%20of%20our%20impressions%20and%20inventory%20because%20of%20their%20very%20long%20engagement%20on%20Reddit%2C%26quot%3B%20Reddit%20Chief%20Operating%20Officer%20Jen%20Wong%20said%20at%20the%20Morgan%20Stanley%20Technology%2C%20Media%2C%20%26amp%3B%20Telecom%20Conference%20in%20March.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20existential%20for%20us%20%E2%80%A6%20I%20think%20the%20business%20is%20extremely%20healthy%20because%2C%20again%2C%20it's%20powered%20by%20the%20logged-in%20users.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReddit%20also%20has%20its%20own%20internal%20AI%20search%20tool%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddit-answers-how-it-works-performs-early-access-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReddit%20Answers%3C%2Fa%3E%2