ts%2C%20requiring%20a%20shift%20in%20how%20they%20are%20trained.%3Cp%3EMeta%20Platforms%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EYann%20LeCun%20says%20there%20are%20four%20traits%20of%20human%20intelligence.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMeta's%20chief%20AI%20scientist%20says%20AI%20lacks%20these%20traits%2C%20requiring%20a%20shift%20in%20training%20methods.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMeta's%20V-JEPA%20is%20a%20non-generative%20AI%20model%20that%20aims%20to%20solve%20the%20problem.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20do%20all%20intelligent%20beings%20have%20in%20common%3F%20Four%20things%2C%20according%20to%20Meta's%20chief%20AI%20scientist%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-yann-lecun-scaling-ai-wont-make-it-smarter-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EYann%20LeCun%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20AI%20Action%20Summit%20in%20Paris%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20political%20leaders%20and%20AI%20experts%20gathered%20to%20discuss%20AI%20development.%20LeCun%20shared%20his%20baseline%20definition%20of%20intelligence%20with%20IBM's%20AI%20leader%2C%20Anthony%20Annunziata.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20four%20essential%20characteristics%20of%20intelligent%20behavior%20that%20every%20animal%2C%20or%20relatively%20smart%20animal%2C%20can%20do%2C%20and%20certainly%20humans%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BUnderstanding%20the%20physical%20world%2C%20having%20persistent%20memory%2C%20being%20able%20to%20reason%2C%20and%20being%20able%20to%20plan%2C%20and%20planning%20complex%20actions%2C%20particularly%20planning%20hierarchically.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeCun%20said%20AI%2C%20especially%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-openai-ai-dictionary-help-understand-nvidia-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elarge%20language%20models%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20have%20not%20hit%20this%20threshold%2C%20and%20incorporating%20these%20capabilities%20would%20require%20a%20shift%20in%20how%20they%20are%20trained.%20That's%20why%20many%20of%20the%20biggest%20tech%20companies%20are%20cobbling%20capabilities%20onto%20existing%20models%20in%20their%20race%20to%20dominate%20the%20AI%20game%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20understanding%20the%20physical%20world%2C%20well%2C%20you%20train%20a%20separate%20vision%20system.%20And%20then%20you%20bolt%20it%20on%20the%20LLM.%20For%20memory%2C%20you%20know%2C%20you%20use%20RAG%2C%20or%20you%20bolt%20some%20associative%20memory%20on%20top%20of%20it%2C%20or%20you%20just%20make%20your%20model%20bigger%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretrieval-augmented-generation-making-ai-language-models-better-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERAG%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20stands%20for%20retrieval%20augmented%20generation%2C%20is%20a%20way%20to%20enhance%20the%20outputs%20of%20large%20language%20models%20using%20external%20knowledge%20sources.%20It%20was%20developed%20at%20Meta.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20those%2C%20however%2C%20are%20just%20%26quot%3Bhacks%2C%26quot%3B%20LeCun%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeCun%20has%20spoken%20on%20several%20occasions%20about%20an%20alternative%20he%20calls%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-yann-lecun-scaling-ai-wont-make-it-smarter-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworld-based%20models%3C%2Fa%3E.%20These%20are%20models%20trained%20on%20real-life%20scenarios%20and%20have%20higher%20levels%20of%20cognition%20than%20pattern-based%20AI.%20LeCun%2C%20in%20his%20chat%20with%20Annunziata%2C%20offered%20another%20definition.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20have%20some%20idea%20of%20the%20state%20of%20the%20world%20at%20time%20T%2C%20you%20imagine%20an%20action%20it%20might%20take%2C%20the%20world%20model%20predicts%20what%20the%20state%20of%20the%20world%20is%20going%20to%20be%20from%20the%20action%20you%20took%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20he%20said%2C%20the%20world%20evolves